result.execSummary:
The defendant Staci A Graves was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse, Use of a Dangerous Weapon], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Cases 14CM398, 15CM16 & 15CM53 called at 2:48pm [mo]
Reserve Judge Sarah O'Brien presiding for Branch IV
Defendant Staci A Graves (Hell) in court with Attorney Yelena Olegovna Zarwell.   ADA Monica Hall appears for the State of Wisconsin.
On Motion of the State, the Court ordrers that Criminal Complaint in case 14CM398 be amended to include 'Also Known As' Staci A. Hell.
Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of "No Contest" entered on Case 14CM398 Count #1, Case 15CM16 Counts #1 & #2 and Case 15CM53 Counts #2 & #4, ; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; the Court accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

Sentencing arguments given by Counsel
Statement made by Ms. Graves (Hell) 
On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses all remaining counts.

As to case 14CM398 Count #1, case 15CM16 Counts #1 & #2 and case 15CM53 counts #2 &#4, the Court withholds sentence, and places Defendant on Probation concurrent on each count for 24 months, with conditions:

--to undergo AODA assessment and follow through with recommended treatment
--to undergo assessment, treatment or counseling as deemed appropriate by the Agent
--to maintain absolute sobriety
--no presence in bars or taverns
--No contact with Joshua Strate unless both defendant and supervising agent approve in advance
--On Case 14CM398 Count #1: to pay costs of $243 plus $100 domestic abuse surcharge  
--On Case 15CM16 Count #1: to pay costs of $243 plus $100 domestic abuse surcharge
--On Case 15CM16 Count #2: to pay costs of $243  
--On Case 15CM53 Count #2: to pay costs of $243 plus $100 domestic abuse surcharge
--On Case 15CM53 Count #4: to pay costs of $243 
The Court does not impose the DNA surcharge, as to all counts 

On Case 15CM16: Days credit for time already served:  2  days

The Court orders the letter from Dean Clinic submitted by Attorney Zarwell be sealed in the file.

(*Direct or indirect contact prohibitions include but are not limited to phone calls, letters, emails, texts, social media, other electronic means and no one can contact the person on your behalf except an attorney.) 
-Maintain absolute sobriety

-No presence at 1153 Boughton St. #22, Watertown (Once Counsel confirm there is a No Contact/Presence provision as part of Mr. Strate's probation conditions, then the no presence condition will be lifted-Counsel to submit proof to the Court)
